OL,7,FStaunton said. "He, on this occasion,
OL,8,Fhas stepped into the realm of the
OL,9,Fgrifter."
OL,11,FMr Staunton said that Hearldon was
OL,12,F'profoundly ashamed' of his behaviour.
OL,14,F"He is a man who wishes, perhaps for
OL,15,Fthe goodness of his redemption, to be
